The disastrous '''General Assembly of Aberdeen''' was held in 1605. A few [[Ministers of the Church of Scotland|ministers]] of the [[Presbyterianism|Presbyterian]] party met in defiance of royal authority<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Duncan|first1=Andrew|editor1-last=Dennison, Jr.|editor1-first=James T.|editor1-link=|title=Rudimenta Pietatis|journal=The Journal of Northwest Theological Seminary|date=December 2007|volume=3|issue=22|pages=35–49|url=http://www.kerux.com/doc/2203A5.asp|accessdate=23 October 2014|publisher=Kerux: The Journal of Northwest Theological Seminary}}</ref> and the [[General Assembly of the Church of Scotland|general assembly]] was prohibited by [[royal proclamation]].

