{{Infobox government cabinet |cabinet_name = Government of the 17th Dáil |cabinet_number = 10th |cabinet_type = Government |jurisdiction = Ireland |incumbent = |image = |image_size = |date_formed = 11 November 1961 |date_dissolved = 21 April 1965 |government_head = [[Seán Lemass]] |government_head_history = |deputy_government_head = [[Seán MacEntee]] |state_head = [[Éamon de Valera]] |current_number = |former_members_number = |total_number = 14 |political_party = [[Fianna Fáil]] |legislature_status = Minority Government |opposition_cabinet = |opposition_party = |opposition_leader = [[James Dillon (Fine Gael politician)|James Dillon]] {{small|([[Fine Gael]])}} |election = [[Irish general election, 1961|1961 general election]] |last_election = |legislature_term = [[17th Dáil]] |budget = |incoming_formation = |outgoing_formation = |previous = [[Government of the 16th Dáil#9th Government of Ireland|9th Government]] |successor = [[Government of the 18th Dáil#11th Government of Ireland|11th Government]] }} The [[17th Dáil]] was elected at the [[Irish general election, 1961|1961 general election]] on 4 October 1961 and first met on 11 November when the 10th [[Government of Ireland]] was appointed. The 17th Dáil lasted for 1,281 days.
