The '''National Council of European Resistance''' ({{lang-fr|Conseil national de la résistance européenne}}, officially abbreviated as '''CNRE''') is a [[France]]-based [[Politics of France|political]] [[Political organization|organization]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.gatestoneinstitute.org/12604/renaud-camus-interview|title=A Conversation with French Writer Renaud Camus|last=Canlorbe|first=Grégoire|work=[[Gatestone Institute]]|access-date=2018-09-29|language=en-US}}</ref>{{Efn|Officially registered as a nonprofit under the French law of 1901.}} that was founded by [[Renaud Camus]] and [[Karim Ouchikh]] on {{start date|9 November 2017}} by analogy to the [[National Council of the Resistance]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.bvoltaire.fr/macron-lincarnation-parfaite-remplacisme-global/|title=Macron est l’incarnation parfaite du remplacisme global|last=Camus|first=Renaud|date=2017-11-13|work=[[Boulevard Voltaire]]|access-date=2017-12-21|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|language=fr-FR}}</ref> It has links to the [[identitarian movement]].<ref name=zuquete group=b>{{Cite book|title=The Identitarians: The Movement against Globalism and Islam in Europe|last=Zúquete|first=José Pedro|publisher=[[University of Notre Dame Press]]|year=2018|isbn=9780268104214|location=[[Notre Dame, Indiana|Notre Dame]]|pages=|asin=0268104212}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Lefebvre|first=Frédéric|date=2018-04-10|title=La "droite identitaire" exige de la "droite décomplexée" qu'elle assume publiquement ses liaisons... |url=https://www.huffingtonpost.fr/fredericlefebvre/identitaires-et-extreme-droite-ces-liaisons-dangereuses-que-la-droite-wauquiez-nassume-pas_a_23406763/|language=fr-fr|agency=[[The Huffington Post]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=La mouvance identitaire manifeste à Paris pour la libération de l'activiste Tommy Robinson|date=2018-06-04||url=https://francais.rt.com/france/51301-manifestation-mouvance-identitaire-paris-liberation-activiste-britannique-tommy-robinson|language=fr-fr|agency=[[RT en français|RT France]]}}</ref>

The Council is intended to bring together qualified French and European personalities who aspire to "work for the defence of [[Western culture|European civilization]]"<ref name=":1">{{Cite news|url=https://www.cnre.eu/charte|title=Charte constitutive|date=2017-12-03|work=Conseil National de la Résistance Européenne|access-date=2017-12-31|language=fr-FR}}</ref>—to oppose the [[Great Replacement]], [[immigration to Europe]], and, more generally, to defeat ''replacist totalitarianism'',<ref name=":1" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.libertepolitique.com/Actualite/Decryptage/Pour-defendre-notre-civilisation-j-appelle-a-un-rassemblement-devant-le-Conseil-d-Etat|title=Pour défendre notre civilisation, j’appelle à un rassemblement devant le Conseil d’Etat|last=Ouchikh|first=Karim|date=2017-12-11|work={{ill|Fondation de service politique|lt=Association pour la Fondation de Service politique|fr|Fondation de service politique}}|language=fr-FR|access-date=2018-01-07}}</ref> a concept theorized by [[Renaud Camus]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.vox.com/world/2017/8/15/16141456/renaud-camus-the-great-replacement-you-will-not-replace-us-charlottesville-white|title=You will not replace us: a French philosopher explains the Charlottesville chant|last=Wildman|first=Sarah|date=2017-08-15|work=[[Vox (website)|Vox]]|access-date=2017-12-31}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/worldviews/wp/2017/12/21/in-2017-nativism-went-mainstream-in-the-west/|title=Analysis {{!}} In 2017, nativism went mainstream in the West|last=Tharoor|first=Ishaan|date=2017-12-21|work=[[The Washington Post]]|access-date=2017-12-31|language=en-US|issn=0190-8286}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |last1=Dupin |first1=Éric |title=La France identitaire : Enquête sur la réaction qui vient |date=2017 |publisher=Éditions La Découverte |location=Paris |isbn=9782707191205}}</ref>

Members of the Council include high-ranking European officials, such as former [[President of the Czech Republic]] [[Václav Klaus]], former [[members of the European Parliament]] [[Jean-Yves Le Gallou]] and [[Paul-Marie Coûteaux]], current [[member of the European Parliament]] [[Janice Atkinson]], and former ''député'' to the [[National Assembly of France]] [[Christian Vanneste]], as well as Africanist historian [[Bernard Lugan]], [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Paris|Roman Catholic]] abbot Father [[Guy Pagès]], and Swiss-American businesswoman [[Eliana Benador]].<ref name=":0" /> It is strictly enlarged by co-option.<ref name=":1" />

== Background ==
{{Trim|{{#section-h:Renaud Camus|The Great Replacement conspiracy theory}}}}

{{Trim|{{#section-h:The Great Replacement conspiracy theory|Origins}}}}

== History ==
In a public address in [[Colombey-les-Deux-Églises]]—the village where [[Charles de Gaulle]] is buried—Renaud Camus announced the foundation of the National Council of European Resistance and asked for a collective European commitment.<ref name=zuquete group=b />

{{Quote|text=All the European nations are invited to lead by our side the fight for the salvation of our common civilization, Celtic, Slavic, Greco-Latin, Judeo-Christian, and free-thinking.|author=Renaud Camus|source=}}

=== Etymology ===
The name ''Conseil national de la résistance européenne'' is a reference to the coordinating body of the [[French Resistance]] during the [[Military history of France during World War II|German occupation of France]]—the [[National Council of the Resistance]].

When asked how the CNRE could be both national and European, [[Renaud Camus]] replied:
{{Quote|text=The Council is national in that each and every nation is responsible for defending its independence and protecting its culture. It is European because our civilisational struggle must be fought in concert with and by all Europeans.|author=Renaud Camus}}

